            "answer_text": "It will depend on what subject(major) you want to pursue your PG . In USA you can opt for M.S in Vet. Biomedical Sciences/Pathobiology/microbiology/parasitology. In Canada you can opt for MSc. or MVSc. Getting into MVSc is difficult for indians because our degree is not AVMA recognized. Australia is good option for masters as here you have chance to get clinical subject for PG.Even Massey University in New zealand used to provide M.S/PG diploma in clinical subjects but for some reasons now they have stopped it and only animal science is available. UC Davis & Cornell are top ranking for veterinary sciences in USA. In Canada Guelph would be best for PG.University of Prince Edward Island offers decent PG courses for Vet Pathology. In NZ Massey is better than other universities. Always prefer universities which are AVMA recognized it will make your further path easier. ",
